WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:03.133
-[line rings]
-AUTOMATED VOICE: You have

00:03.177 --> 00:04.439
reached
the voice-mail box of...

00:04.482 --> 00:06.876
-CHIP: Chip from Baskets.
-At the tone,

00:06.919 --> 00:09.052
-please record
your voice message.
-[beep]

00:09.096 --> 00:11.315
Hey, Chip. It's Martha.

00:11.359 --> 00:17.278
Um, I've called a few timesand, uh, didn't leave a message.

00:17.321 --> 00:20.237
Um, are you mad at me?

00:20.281 --> 00:23.458
I'm not sure
what happened, but, um...

00:23.501 --> 00:26.069
but I apologize
if I did anything.

00:26.113 --> 00:29.203
Um, I heard that
the rodeo's shutting down,

00:29.246 --> 00:32.119
and so maybe
you just need some space,

00:32.162 --> 00:36.079
um, or maybe you need
to talk to somebody,

00:36.123 --> 00:39.952
and if that's, uh, the case,
uh, just give me a jangle.

00:39.996 --> 00:41.519
-Um...
-[line beeps]

00:41.563 --> 00:43.304
Oh.

00:50.354 --> 00:51.790
Did I tell you
the cats really missed you?

00:51.834 --> 00:53.357
'Cause Ronald Reagan,

00:53.401 --> 00:55.533
I found him sleeping
in your undies drawer.

00:55.577 --> 00:57.100
[sighs]:
Oh.

00:57.144 --> 00:59.972
Ah, I'm just glad that
the carpet emergency is over.

01:00.016 --> 01:02.366
I am, too, honey,
and you did really good.

01:02.410 --> 01:04.325
I'm really proud of you,
but I really missed you.

01:04.368 --> 01:06.544
[chuckles softly]
Thanks.

01:06.588 --> 01:09.982
-We sure about this move, baby?-Oh, honey, yeah.

01:10.026 --> 01:13.116
You know,I never really liked this place.

01:13.160 --> 01:16.511
Well, I will call the broker
and see if I can list it.

01:16.554 --> 01:19.296
Oh, please do, and find out whatkind of beat we're gonna take

01:19.340 --> 01:21.168
on that damn equity thing.

01:21.211 --> 01:22.691
-[ringtone playing]
-[groans]

01:22.734 --> 01:25.259
Who wants what? Oh, God.

01:25.302 --> 01:27.043
Hey, Martha.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.698
Hey, Mrs. Baskets.
Have you heard from Chip?

01:29.741 --> 01:33.354
No. You know, honey,
he's a brooder.

01:33.397 --> 01:35.965
You got to give him time.
He'll come around.

01:36.008 --> 01:39.360
Are you sure he's not upset
about losing the rodeo?

01:39.403 --> 01:41.188
We're all upset, honey.

01:41.231 --> 01:44.147
It worked out the way it did,
and you have to live with it.

01:44.191 --> 01:45.627
He'll come around.

01:45.670 --> 01:49.413
But I've got some exciting news:Ken and I are moving to Denver.

01:49.457 --> 01:53.722
Wow. This is a lot
of info to process.

01:53.765 --> 01:55.593
Well, you're telling me.
I'm a California girl

01:55.637 --> 01:59.554
going to a cold climate andI don't even have a winter coat.

01:59.597 --> 02:02.426
Oh. Hi, Susan.

02:02.470 --> 02:05.734
Susan's here. You know, that catreminds me of you, Martha.

02:05.777 --> 02:08.258
Hey, Martha,
where could I get a good coat?

02:08.302 --> 02:10.608
Um, I think
Burlington Coat Factory

02:10.652 --> 02:12.219
is known for their coats.

02:12.262 --> 02:14.438
Oh, that's so perfect.

02:14.482 --> 02:16.962
Martha, I'm gonna miss you
and all the kids.

02:17.006 --> 02:19.095
But I guess you have
your own lives now,

02:19.139 --> 02:21.837
but I hope we stay in touch.

02:21.880 --> 02:25.275
Well, do you want to, like,
exchange addresses

02:25.319 --> 02:27.408
and be pen pals or something?

02:27.451 --> 02:29.975
No, honey,
there's no writing letters.

02:30.019 --> 02:31.194
Take a flight.

02:31.238 --> 02:33.196
Get one of those
cheapie airline flights

02:33.240 --> 02:35.894
like on Southwest or Spirit.

02:35.938 --> 02:38.897
-Um, yeah,
I don't really like South...
-I love you, Martha.

02:38.941 --> 02:41.248
Hang in there.
Chip will come around.

02:41.291 --> 02:42.466
-Bye, honey.
-[line clicks]

02:42.510 --> 02:44.164
Uhp, she hung up.

02:46.253 --> 02:48.124
[sighs]

02:49.169 --> 02:51.867
♪

02:51.910 --> 02:53.390
Hi.

03:07.535 --> 03:11.234
Chip, I heard about the rodeo
and your mom moving away.

03:11.278 --> 03:13.280
It sounds like a lot.

03:16.631 --> 03:19.677
I think maybe you're annoyed
with me 'cause I asked

03:19.721 --> 03:23.377
if you were mad at me,
but I brought you something.

03:23.420 --> 03:25.727
It's kind of an olive branch.

03:25.770 --> 03:28.338
Hello. Can I help you?

03:28.382 --> 03:30.253
Hang on, Chip.
I've got a situation.

03:30.297 --> 03:32.255
Hi.

03:32.299 --> 03:34.475
Were you here
to see the place, or...?

03:34.518 --> 03:36.041
Kind of.

03:36.085 --> 03:37.826
[alarm beeps quietly]

03:37.869 --> 03:39.828
Wow, he decorated.

03:39.871 --> 03:42.700
Oh, the-the apartment's forsale, so the furniture is fake.

03:42.744 --> 03:44.354
-But...
-Well, it looks real.

03:44.398 --> 03:47.357
-Wait, he moved out?
-Yeah, I know, right?

03:47.401 --> 03:50.491
He's never gonna walk
to the bullet train station.

03:50.534 --> 03:53.755
Well, did he leave aforwarding address or anything?

03:53.798 --> 03:56.540
I believe he did.
I can look it up.

03:56.584 --> 03:58.194
Okay.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.718
Um, do you want a hat rack?

04:00.762 --> 04:03.504
That's okay.

04:03.547 --> 04:05.375
I'll look the address up.

04:07.595 --> 04:09.597
♪

04:16.038 --> 04:17.561
[blows softly]

04:34.056 --> 04:36.058
[water trickling]

04:38.713 --> 04:40.671
TAMMY:
There's nothing like it,
is there?

04:40.715 --> 04:42.194
I mean, it's so peaceful.

04:42.238 --> 04:45.502
And we're growing everything
for ourselves.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.722
Oh, and look, that's a loquat.

04:47.765 --> 04:49.985
Looks like a large kumquat.

04:50.028 --> 04:52.030
Yeah, but it's a loquat.

04:52.074 --> 04:54.163
What do they taste like?

04:54.206 --> 04:56.426
Like, um, a kiwi.

05:01.388 --> 05:04.216
Or kind of like kumquat.

05:04.260 --> 05:06.262
♪

05:13.225 --> 05:14.705
MARTHA:
Sorry to bother you.

05:14.749 --> 05:16.490
TAMMY:
Oh, it's no bother at all.

05:16.533 --> 05:18.622
I was just out backpicking these fabulous tomatoes.

05:18.666 --> 05:21.582
You really ought to try one.
They are incredible.

05:21.625 --> 05:23.410
No, thanks, Tammy.

05:23.453 --> 05:25.412
Um, I'm looking for Chip.

05:26.761 --> 05:28.502
Really?

05:28.545 --> 05:30.417
And why is that?

05:30.460 --> 05:32.984
Um, a lot of reasons.

05:33.028 --> 05:35.552
I don't know exactly, um...

05:36.858 --> 05:39.382
I think I do.

05:39.426 --> 05:42.603
You're worried about him
and you care about him.

05:42.646 --> 05:44.779
Is he here?

05:46.084 --> 05:49.566
I'm not at liberty to say.

05:49.610 --> 05:52.526
But I can tell you
that he's finally serious

05:52.569 --> 05:55.050
about working on himself.

05:55.093 --> 05:58.314
Well, I really want
to speak to him.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.621
Did he contact you?

06:00.664 --> 06:03.232
No.

06:03.275 --> 06:06.583
Martha, have you considered
that you might be

06:06.627 --> 06:08.455
overidentified with Chip

06:08.498 --> 06:11.545
and that you're sublimating
your own issues

06:11.588 --> 06:14.069
by coming out here to save him?

06:14.112 --> 06:16.332
[Tammy sighs]

06:16.376 --> 06:19.640
He really needs
to go through this on his own,

06:19.683 --> 06:22.643
and it's best
that you leave him alone.

06:28.126 --> 06:29.389
Dear...

06:31.695 --> 06:33.393
...go home.

06:39.877 --> 06:41.357
[door opens]

06:41.401 --> 06:43.054
[sighs]

06:43.098 --> 06:44.621
[door closes]

06:51.193 --> 06:55.153
Dale? Dale?

06:55.197 --> 06:57.678
Dale, is that you--

06:57.721 --> 06:59.680
Sorry.

06:59.723 --> 07:01.464
Excuse me, sir.

07:01.508 --> 07:03.684
Sir, do you know Dale?

07:03.727 --> 07:05.120
You IRS?

07:05.163 --> 07:08.123
No, sir, I'm just looking
for Dale Baskets.

07:08.166 --> 07:10.168
I thought I smelled
a nice perfume

07:10.212 --> 07:11.648
wafting through the RV park.

07:11.692 --> 07:13.607
What is that, Lady Old Spice?

07:13.650 --> 07:16.566
Dale, something serious
is going on.

07:16.610 --> 07:18.046
Martha, is this
a ploy of some sort?

07:18.089 --> 07:19.830
Do you still have
feelings for me?

07:19.874 --> 07:21.092
[groans]
Not now.

07:21.136 --> 07:24.400
-Can we talk?
-Okay.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.533
Well, it sounds like
she's brainwashing him.

07:26.576 --> 07:28.535
MARTHA:
Well, not exactly.

07:28.578 --> 07:31.581
I mean,
it's supposed to help him.

07:31.625 --> 07:33.104
She's helped a lot of people.

07:33.148 --> 07:35.629
You just give her
a few thousand dollars

07:35.672 --> 07:37.282
and move into her compound,
and then...

07:37.326 --> 07:39.067
Uh, you give her
a few thousand dollars

07:39.110 --> 07:40.764
and move into her compound?

07:40.808 --> 07:43.375
-Just a few, huh?
-He's in a cult, Martha.

07:43.419 --> 07:44.986
He's in a cult.

07:45.029 --> 07:47.597
He may be one of 100 husbands
to this woman right now.

07:47.641 --> 07:49.643
That's right. Or even
if he's the fifth husband,

07:49.686 --> 07:52.863
-I have a problem with that.
-MARTHA: Oh, my God.

07:52.907 --> 07:56.780
This is crazy.What are we gonna do about Chip?

07:56.824 --> 07:59.914
-We can lure him out.
-Wait, how will we do that?

07:59.957 --> 08:02.090
Sugar cubes.

08:02.133 --> 08:03.526
For Chip?

08:03.570 --> 08:06.137
Sugar activates theopiate receptors in your brain.

08:06.181 --> 08:08.139
People can't resist it.

08:08.183 --> 08:11.316
That's why women eat so much
chocolate on their periods.

08:11.360 --> 08:14.885
Anything he likes, what do you
know that he is very fond of?

08:14.929 --> 08:17.540
-[fly buzzes]
-[clattering]

08:17.584 --> 08:20.238
Okay. I think I know
what he likes.

08:20.282 --> 08:22.240
[piano playing gentle melody]

08:22.284 --> 08:23.938
PENELOPE:
♪ You know me♪

08:26.941 --> 08:30.422
♪ Oh, you know me♪

08:31.815 --> 08:35.602
♪ You know me♪

08:35.645 --> 08:37.821
♪ Too well♪

08:37.865 --> 08:42.783
♪ But if all those petty fears♪

08:42.826 --> 08:47.483
♪ Make every woman blind♪

08:47.527 --> 08:49.833
♪ Every woman♪

08:49.877 --> 08:52.749
♪ Blind.♪

08:52.793 --> 08:54.446
[music stops]

08:54.490 --> 08:57.058
[muffled]:
Hey, Penelope. Sounds good.

08:57.101 --> 08:58.755
PENELOPE:
Martha.

08:58.799 --> 09:00.757
-I love your style.
-Oh, thanks, Penelope.

09:00.801 --> 09:02.846
-You don't want any tea?
-Oh, no, thanks.

09:02.890 --> 09:06.415
I stopped at Starbucksfour times on the way down here,

09:06.458 --> 09:08.417
so I'm kind of jacked.

09:08.460 --> 09:10.637
Okay.

09:10.680 --> 09:14.641
Um, I can't believe
Chip is in a cult.

09:14.684 --> 09:17.165
-Yeah.
-It doesn't
sound like him at all.

09:17.208 --> 09:22.736
And I wonder if it's not just
a performance or something,

09:22.779 --> 09:24.738
like, a clowning, you know?

09:24.781 --> 09:26.261
Um, I don't know.

09:26.304 --> 09:28.872
Uh, the last I heard,
he gave up "clooning."

09:28.916 --> 09:30.961
Oh.

09:31.005 --> 09:33.442
Well, so, what can I do?

09:35.705 --> 09:38.447
PENELOPE:
Chip.

09:38.490 --> 09:40.014
Penelope,
what are you doing here?

09:40.057 --> 09:43.670
What are you doing here?

09:43.713 --> 09:45.672
How are you?
I tried calling.

09:45.715 --> 09:47.021
Oh, I threw out my cell phone.

09:47.064 --> 09:48.283
-Oh.
-Yeah.

09:48.326 --> 09:50.938
Nice. Are you a farmer now?

09:53.897 --> 09:55.899
I mean, what are you doing?

09:55.943 --> 09:58.815
Well, I'm just, you know,
I'm just trying to...

09:58.859 --> 10:02.863
refocus my brain, in a way.

10:02.906 --> 10:04.865
Um, I... I'm medit--

10:04.908 --> 10:06.910
-I know it sounds ridiculous
coming from me.
-No, no.

10:06.954 --> 10:08.651
But I'm med-- I'm meditating,

10:08.695 --> 10:11.915
and, yeah, it's silly,
but it seems to-- I like it.

10:11.959 --> 10:13.438
I do.

10:13.482 --> 10:15.527
-What happened to your clowning?-[insect buzzes]

10:15.571 --> 10:18.748
You always said I was
a bad clown. Is that a bee?

10:18.792 --> 10:21.708
[laughing]
No.

10:21.751 --> 10:23.884
-Did I miss it?
-Look.

10:23.927 --> 10:26.800
You're funny. You're a clown,
whatever you do.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.323
TAMMY:
Penelope.

10:28.366 --> 10:30.673
Penelope, Chip is healing here.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.675
I think it's time for you to go.

10:32.719 --> 10:35.112
Oh, really?

10:35.156 --> 10:37.724
Um, yes, I just wanted
to show him something

10:37.767 --> 10:38.942
that I bought for him.

10:38.986 --> 10:40.117
Okay.

10:40.161 --> 10:43.947
You want to-- I'll show you.

10:43.991 --> 10:46.950
Okay, sure, sure, yeah.

10:46.994 --> 10:48.125
It's a beautiful place here.

10:48.169 --> 10:50.301
-Yeah, she's had it
for a, for a while.
-Oh.

10:50.345 --> 10:51.607
-I'm sorry, Chip.
-What is this?

10:51.651 --> 10:52.739
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

10:52.782 --> 10:54.610
What's going on?!
Let go of me!

10:54.654 --> 10:56.960
-I'm so sorry, so sorry.
-Penelope, what's going on?!

10:57.004 --> 10:59.267
Martha, is that you?! Martha!

10:59.310 --> 11:02.183
-Dale, I can smell your cologne!-DALE: Shut up, sissy!

11:02.226 --> 11:04.272
-[gunshot]
-[Martha screams]
-DALE: Oh, stray bullet!

11:04.315 --> 11:06.578
-Martha!
-In the van! Get in the van!

11:06.622 --> 11:07.928
-M-Martha's on the ground!
-She's fine.

11:07.971 --> 11:09.277
-Go, guys!
-Martha.
-[engine starts]

11:09.320 --> 11:10.321
DALE:
Go, go, go!

11:10.365 --> 11:12.541
[Dale laughing]

11:12.584 --> 11:15.326
[shouting in French]

11:15.370 --> 11:16.893
Oh. Are you okay?

11:22.769 --> 11:23.987
[saw buzzing]

11:36.347 --> 11:37.827
MRS. BASKETS:
Martha.

11:37.871 --> 11:40.787
-What happened?
-Hi, Mrs. Baskets.

11:40.830 --> 11:43.746
I brought you some flowers.
They say it cheers people up.

11:43.790 --> 11:45.922
I don't like 'em myself, but...

11:45.966 --> 11:48.403
-Well, thanks.
-[sighs]

11:48.446 --> 11:51.798
Hey, um, I'm really sorry
about Chip.

11:51.841 --> 11:53.190
What about Chip?

11:53.234 --> 11:55.758
Well, all the stuff with Tammy.

11:55.802 --> 11:58.935
Tammy? W-What?

11:58.979 --> 12:02.678
Um, I introduced Chip
to my life coach.

12:02.722 --> 12:06.377
You know, like, haven't you
noticed a difference in me?

12:06.421 --> 12:09.598
Well, I thought
it would help Chip, too.

12:09.641 --> 12:12.906
I introduced them, and then
he just took it a lot farther

12:12.949 --> 12:16.170
than I thought he would
and moved up there

12:16.213 --> 12:19.782
and paid her a bunch of money
to pick vegetables

12:19.826 --> 12:21.784
and he sold his condo.

12:21.828 --> 12:23.264
[groans]:
Oh.

12:23.307 --> 12:25.788
[breathes deeply]

12:25.832 --> 12:27.050
[mutters softly]

12:29.052 --> 12:31.838
I got to sit down.

12:31.881 --> 12:34.928
[sighs]:
Oh.

12:34.971 --> 12:37.234
Sold the condo?

12:39.236 --> 12:41.673
That kid.

12:41.717 --> 12:42.805
[clicks tongue]

12:42.849 --> 12:44.328
[sighs]

12:49.420 --> 12:51.379
-DALE: Hey, mama.
-MRS. BASKETS: Hey, honey.

12:51.422 --> 12:53.511
-How is he?-Well, I had to lock his ass up.

12:53.555 --> 12:55.818
He's a danger to himself
and society.

12:55.862 --> 12:57.689
KEN:
Are you okay?

12:59.691 --> 13:01.302
Yeah.

13:04.218 --> 13:05.480
Chip?

13:08.091 --> 13:10.137
-Chip?
-[goat bleats]

13:11.921 --> 13:13.923
Oh, Lord, Lord, Lord.

13:15.316 --> 13:17.274
Mom, finally you're here.

13:17.318 --> 13:20.103
-Listen, I-I'm not in a cult.
-[goat bleats]

13:20.147 --> 13:22.845
I-I-I don't need this. Okay?

13:22.889 --> 13:24.847
And-and how's Martha,
by the way?

13:24.891 --> 13:27.763
It's worse than I thought.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.765
What is?

13:29.809 --> 13:32.202
-Honey, are you even in there?
-What?

13:32.246 --> 13:34.901
What did they give you?
Cough syrup?

13:34.944 --> 13:38.121
Some sort of s-special syrup?

13:38.165 --> 13:41.124
Some sort of breakfast
with stuff in it?

13:41.168 --> 13:43.083
Are you done with
your line of questioning?

13:43.126 --> 13:45.433
Well, honey, I'm just trying
to get to the bottom

13:45.476 --> 13:46.869
of what happened to my son Chip.

13:46.913 --> 13:48.915
He's right here,
but I happen to be

13:48.958 --> 13:50.960
-in a freaking goat prison!
-[goat bleats]

13:51.004 --> 13:54.311
Honey, is this all
because of Sacramento?

13:54.355 --> 13:57.575
-Are you mad about that?
-No, I'm just...

13:57.619 --> 13:59.926
I'm trying to do something
different, Mom, okay?

13:59.969 --> 14:03.016
And I'm just, you know, trying
to find out who I really am.

14:03.059 --> 14:06.106
You're Chip Baskets.

14:06.149 --> 14:08.021
Chip Baskets.

14:08.064 --> 14:10.066
Now stop being so ridiculous.

14:10.110 --> 14:12.155
My...

14:12.199 --> 14:14.114
Mom, my-my feelings
are not ridiculous.

14:14.157 --> 14:16.333
When you went to sell the rodeowithout even consulting me,

14:16.377 --> 14:19.249
I felt erased.
I'm not an extension of you.

14:19.293 --> 14:22.035
Is this you talkingor is this that Tiffany talking?

14:22.078 --> 14:23.732
Her name is Tammy.

14:23.775 --> 14:25.734
Is this Tammy talking
or you talking?

14:25.777 --> 14:28.128
It's me talking, Mom.

14:28.171 --> 14:31.044
Where is she, Chip?
I need an address.

14:31.087 --> 14:32.306
I don't...

14:32.349 --> 14:35.135
Mom, do not talk to her.

14:35.178 --> 14:37.398
Mom, please.

14:37.441 --> 14:38.703
Where is she?

14:38.747 --> 14:41.837
-Do not talk to her.
-I'll find her.

14:41.881 --> 14:43.099
-I will.
-Mom. Mom.

14:43.143 --> 14:46.015
I'm gonna find her. I-I will...

14:46.059 --> 14:48.409
Chip. Chip.

14:48.452 --> 14:50.759
It's a good thing
you are locked up.

14:52.630 --> 14:54.371
Grabbing your mother!

14:56.025 --> 14:57.592
[goat bleats]

15:00.638 --> 15:03.163
Okay, this is
the hole in one, girls.

15:03.206 --> 15:05.992
-[laughing]
-Don't you doubt me.

15:06.035 --> 15:07.994
[laughs]

15:08.037 --> 15:10.083
[vehicle whirring in distance]

15:10.126 --> 15:12.085
What's that?

15:14.130 --> 15:16.959
Can you please get off
the center of the fairway?

15:17.003 --> 15:19.527
MAN: Ladies, can we get
this show on the road?

15:19.570 --> 15:21.572
Well, I would love to,
but there seems to be

15:21.616 --> 15:24.053
some kind of commotion
on the green.

15:24.097 --> 15:26.795
-See?
-Move!

15:26.838 --> 15:29.580
What have you done to my son?

15:29.624 --> 15:31.147
Oh, no.

15:31.191 --> 15:33.976
You're stopping up
the whole golf course.

15:34.020 --> 15:35.195
Well, it's her fault!

15:35.238 --> 15:37.849
She brainwashed my son,

15:37.893 --> 15:40.330
and I'm not leaving here
till I get some answers.

15:40.374 --> 15:42.854
It's okay, everybody.
I've got this under control.

15:42.898 --> 15:45.031
Know what?
We're just gonna go on ahead.

15:45.074 --> 15:46.249
-Excuse me.
-[sighs]

15:46.293 --> 15:48.469
Enjoy your soap opera.

15:48.512 --> 15:51.124
You must be Christine Baskets.

15:51.167 --> 15:55.128
You're exactly the way
Chip described you.

15:55.171 --> 15:58.261
Well, I'm really sorry, but
I have no idea where Chip is.

15:58.305 --> 16:01.482
He walked away from my house andhe hasn't contacted me since.

16:01.525 --> 16:06.269
Well, you're responsible
for whatever happens to Chip.

16:06.313 --> 16:08.663
Chip is his own person.

16:08.706 --> 16:10.186
He's making his own choices,

16:10.230 --> 16:12.841
and frankly they're
very good ones right now.

16:12.884 --> 16:15.148
So if you hear from him
or you see him,

16:15.191 --> 16:17.411
just tell him that
I'd love for him to come back.

16:17.454 --> 16:21.067
The door is open.
For you, too, by the way.

16:21.110 --> 16:24.026
Ha! Good one.

16:24.070 --> 16:26.246
Is that how she got you ladies?

16:26.289 --> 16:28.422
Are you part of the cult?

16:28.465 --> 16:30.598
Are you in a trance right now?

16:30.641 --> 16:33.122
-[chuckles]
-Mm.

16:33.166 --> 16:35.081
They look really out of it.

16:35.124 --> 16:37.300
Christine...

16:37.344 --> 16:41.174
do you really want Chip
living at home with you

16:41.217 --> 16:43.393
for the rest of his life?

16:43.437 --> 16:47.267
He wants to improve himself
if you'll let him.

16:47.310 --> 16:49.051
I did let him improve himself.

16:49.095 --> 16:53.055
I gave him the money for
the down payment on the condo.

16:53.099 --> 16:55.840
Where do you think he got
the money that he gave you?

16:55.884 --> 16:57.059
It was from me.

16:57.103 --> 17:01.107
And that wasn't his money
to give to some charlatan.

17:01.150 --> 17:04.893
He likes what I have to offer.
A lot of people do.

17:04.936 --> 17:07.504
He likes shiny things.

17:07.548 --> 17:09.985
Well, he signed a contract
with us.

17:11.987 --> 17:14.294
-Do you want to be his mommy?
-No.

17:14.337 --> 17:18.080
No. I'm his mommy.
He's already got one.

17:18.124 --> 17:20.430
And you're gonna do him
more damage

17:20.474 --> 17:23.259
day after day after day.

17:23.303 --> 17:26.175
-Mm-hmm.
-I can see it in your eyes.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.094
♪

17:36.229 --> 17:38.100
-[lock clicking]
-Oh.

17:38.144 --> 17:39.275
What's going on?

17:39.319 --> 17:40.711
-Get over here.
-What?

17:40.755 --> 17:42.104
-I want to spank you!
-Mom!

17:42.148 --> 17:43.540
-What are you doing? Ow!
-[muttering]

17:43.584 --> 17:45.325
-I am so mad at you!
-Ow!
-[goat bleats]

17:45.368 --> 17:48.502
-Mom, what are you-- Stop!
-Why would you give that woman
all that money?!

17:48.545 --> 17:52.375
It's my money.
I can do what I want, Mom.

17:52.419 --> 17:54.725
My buttocks is killing me.

17:54.769 --> 17:58.555
For God's sakes, this woman
doesn't care about you.

17:58.599 --> 18:02.255
She's taking advantage
of a vulnerable person.

18:02.298 --> 18:06.172
-[sighs]
-You know, sometimes I think
you just wantto fail at life.

18:06.215 --> 18:09.000
Oh, really? Like I, like I
f-failed at-at clown college

18:09.044 --> 18:10.698
and I fail at the rodeo?

18:10.741 --> 18:12.526
Oh, God.

18:12.569 --> 18:14.354
Well, you got to go
to clown college.

18:14.397 --> 18:16.269
You got a rodeo.

18:16.312 --> 18:20.360
Or-or-or maybe
my-my-my marriage failed

18:20.403 --> 18:22.362
because of me?

18:22.405 --> 18:26.757
Another woman who was trying
to take advantage of you.

18:26.801 --> 18:29.499
Do you think she loved you?

18:29.543 --> 18:32.415
I mean, she was a lovely personand very beautiful,

18:32.459 --> 18:36.724
talented and all the rest,
but...

18:36.767 --> 18:38.856
I don't think
she cared about you.

18:38.900 --> 18:41.076
Mom...

18:41.120 --> 18:44.732
you need to accept the fact
that you...

18:44.775 --> 18:47.256
you don't always know
what's best for me.

18:47.300 --> 18:50.303
Ever since Dad died,
you've been trying to fix me.

18:50.346 --> 18:53.306
You know who
you should've fixed? Dad.

18:53.349 --> 18:55.569
-But I mean fixed down here.
You know what I mean?
-Oh...

18:55.612 --> 18:57.440
'Cause that way, you-you guys
would've never had me

18:57.484 --> 18:59.573
and what's-his-face.

18:59.616 --> 19:02.184
Dale. [exhales]

19:02.228 --> 19:04.665
[sighs]

19:04.708 --> 19:06.710
♪

19:09.278 --> 19:11.237
I'm sorry, Chip.

19:11.280 --> 19:14.762
I'm sorry, 'cause
when your dad died,

19:14.805 --> 19:19.245
I was just trying to protect youfrom all the pain.

19:19.288 --> 19:21.682
Maybe I wastrying to fix you.
I don't know.

19:21.725 --> 19:25.381
Or maybe I was just trying
to feel better myself.

19:25.425 --> 19:28.428
I know this:

19:28.471 --> 19:32.083
that those people
don't care about you.

19:32.127 --> 19:35.261
They're not your family.
[sighs]

19:40.744 --> 19:43.399
Wonder where that goat went.

19:46.315 --> 19:48.709
-[goat bleats]
-Oh, there's that old goat.

19:48.752 --> 19:50.450
-[chuckles]
-He's up to mischief. [laughs]

19:50.493 --> 19:52.452
Ah, they say they'll eat
anything, won't they?

19:52.495 --> 19:54.323
-Yeah, they'll eat anything.
-[chuckles]

19:54.367 --> 19:55.846
You know, Dale,
that's pretty nice,

19:55.890 --> 19:58.371
the way you went so far out
for your brother.

19:58.414 --> 20:00.242
Sometimes you go
a little too far,

20:00.286 --> 20:02.810
-but it's really nice.
-[quietly]: Well...

20:02.853 --> 20:05.378
You're a really good brother,
you know that?

20:05.421 --> 20:09.251
Well, don't try to butter me uptoo much, Ken. [chuckles]

20:09.295 --> 20:11.122
[sniffs]

20:12.298 --> 20:15.301
-You ever had goat's milk?
-On my cereal.

20:15.344 --> 20:16.867
Oh.

20:18.217 --> 20:20.088
I once drank it
straight from the teat

20:20.131 --> 20:22.395
at my Aunt Helen's house
when I was a kid.

20:24.701 --> 20:27.269
MRS. BASKETS:
I love you, Chip.

20:27.313 --> 20:31.839
And I have spent the majority
of my life trying to help you.

20:31.882 --> 20:34.320
You're my precious boy.

20:37.366 --> 20:41.196
Yeah, well, that's just it, Mom.I'm not, I'm not a boy.

20:41.240 --> 20:43.154
I'm a grown-up.

20:43.198 --> 20:46.157
And I'm a clown, you know?

20:46.201 --> 20:50.292
And when I clown, sometimes
I fall and slip on a banana.

20:50.336 --> 20:53.295
And I get back up, and,
you know, I step on a rake,

20:53.339 --> 20:55.297
and it hits me in the face.

20:55.341 --> 21:00.389
But I get up again,
just like I do as a grown-up.

21:00.433 --> 21:03.479
I just want you to treat me...

21:06.395 --> 21:08.179
...like an adult.

21:08.223 --> 21:10.530
And I'll do the same for you.

21:10.573 --> 21:14.098
Well, you can't
give that woman that money.

21:14.142 --> 21:16.666
I know.

21:16.710 --> 21:20.191
Sorry about grabbing
your... your outfit earlier.

21:20.235 --> 21:22.455
♪

21:22.498 --> 21:25.458
Well, it's pretty strong.

21:25.501 --> 21:27.373
And I'm sorry about
spanking you.

21:27.416 --> 21:30.985
I'm sure I'm gonna have welts
in my left buttocks cheek.

21:31.028 --> 21:33.335
Well, you're all
grown up now, so...

21:33.379 --> 21:35.076
take care of those welts.

21:41.778 --> 21:43.171
[TV playing quietly]

21:43.214 --> 21:44.738
Hey, I'm looking
for Martha Brooks.

21:44.781 --> 21:46.566
-Oh, hey, Chip.
-[TV volume decreases]

21:46.609 --> 21:47.958
Got you these.
Where would you like them?

21:48.002 --> 21:51.222
Oh, wow.
Um, well, actually...

21:51.266 --> 21:53.573
-I'll put-- you want me
to put them over here?
-Yeah.

21:53.616 --> 21:55.401
Mm-hmm.

21:56.445 --> 21:58.839
[balloons pop]

21:58.882 --> 22:01.015
How's your arm?

22:01.058 --> 22:03.191
It still works.

22:03.234 --> 22:07.630
You know, that cast
saved your arm's life.

22:07.674 --> 22:10.372
Yeah, I guess
carpal tunnel has its perks.

22:10.416 --> 22:11.982
[smacks lips]

22:12.026 --> 22:13.897
[monitor beeping steadily]

22:15.899 --> 22:20.295
Um... I'm really sorry about
all that stuff with Tammy

22:20.339 --> 22:22.863
and Dale and...
all the roughhousing.

22:22.906 --> 22:25.082
Just got out of hand.

22:25.126 --> 22:28.434
I, uh... uh, maybe I got
out of hand, too, you know?

22:28.477 --> 22:30.566
There's just...

22:30.610 --> 22:32.612
just a lot of changes.

22:32.655 --> 22:34.614
Mom's moving to Denver.

22:34.657 --> 22:36.529
You're not moving to Denver,
are you?

22:36.572 --> 22:39.706
Mm-mm. No.
I have no reason to.

22:41.708 --> 22:43.840
Okay, well,
thanks for coming, Chip,

22:43.884 --> 22:46.103
but I was watching
Judge Joe Brown

22:46.147 --> 22:47.627
before you got here,
and I think

22:47.670 --> 22:51.544
they're about to announce
the verdict, so maybe...

22:51.587 --> 22:54.285
That's it for the visit?

22:54.329 --> 22:56.549
I-I've been here
for two minutes.

22:56.592 --> 22:58.202
Scoot over.

22:58.246 --> 23:00.248
-What do you mean?
-Scooch.

23:02.076 --> 23:04.034
What's this case about?

23:04.078 --> 23:06.776
-Uh...
-Sorry..

23:06.820 --> 23:11.694
Well, um, it's this guy says
that the lady took his money,

23:11.738 --> 23:14.131
but she says that
he was her boyfriend

23:14.175 --> 23:17.091
-and he loaned it to her.
-Hmm.

23:17.134 --> 23:19.136
♪

23:21.138 --> 23:24.446
-You think the nurse
will bring in some popcorn?
-No.

23:24.490 --> 23:26.535
♪ I know you♪

23:29.669 --> 23:32.106
♪ I know you...♪

23:32.149 --> 23:34.543
MRS. BASKETS:
Dale. Would you
help your mother?

23:34.587 --> 23:36.937
-Yeah, I'll give you a shove.
-Oh, thank you, honey.

23:36.980 --> 23:39.069
-I love this shawl
that you wear.
-Ready?

23:39.113 --> 23:41.245
-Isn't it something?
-Here, Mom. It's beautiful.

23:41.289 --> 23:43.639
Oh. It's part tiger,
part rainbow.

23:43.683 --> 23:45.641
-[chuckles]
-[groans]

23:45.685 --> 23:46.903
[sighs]:
Ooh.

23:46.947 --> 23:49.036
Well, best of luck to you.

23:49.079 --> 23:51.255
I'll be back before you know it.

23:51.299 --> 23:52.692
Well, take your time.

23:52.735 --> 23:54.737
You're always funny.

23:54.781 --> 23:58.045
KEN:
Could someone give me a hand
with these last few suitcases?

23:58.088 --> 24:01.527
-Well, I'm already in.
-Yeah, I'll be right there.

24:01.570 --> 24:04.530
Well, Mom, all the squeaky toysare accounted for.

24:04.573 --> 24:06.749
Oh, the kitties will be happy
about that.

24:06.793 --> 24:10.318
What are you gonna do, honey?

24:10.361 --> 24:13.930
[sighs] You know, I don't know,and I feel pretty good about it.

24:13.974 --> 24:15.541
That's a good attitude.

24:15.584 --> 24:17.412
-I like that.
-I'll give you...

24:19.414 --> 24:23.157
What are you coming in to--Oh, you're gonna give me a hug.

24:23.200 --> 24:24.767
You're so sweet.

24:24.811 --> 24:26.377
Bye, Mom.

24:26.421 --> 24:29.119
-I love you.
-I love you, Chip.

24:32.253 --> 24:33.602
[sighs]

24:34.951 --> 24:37.563
-Bye, Dad.
-[chuckles] Bye, son.

24:37.606 --> 24:39.434
-Take care.
-Take care of Mom.

24:39.478 --> 24:41.523
I will.

24:41.567 --> 24:43.003
♪ You know me...♪

24:43.046 --> 24:44.700
-KEN: You ready, baby?
-MRS. BASKETS: Ready, baby.

24:44.744 --> 24:45.962
KEN:
Let's do it.

24:46.006 --> 24:47.790
MRS. BASKETS:
Let's hit the road, Jack.

24:47.834 --> 24:49.357
-I mean Ken.
-[Ken laughs]

24:52.621 --> 24:55.406
Well, we finally chased her
out of town, didn't we?

24:55.450 --> 24:57.408
[chuckles]

24:57.452 --> 24:58.758
Peace out.

24:58.801 --> 25:02.588
♪ Too well♪

25:02.631 --> 25:05.025
♪ But if all those♪

25:05.068 --> 25:07.767
♪ Petty fears♪

25:07.810 --> 25:11.466
♪ Make every woman♪

25:11.510 --> 25:12.815
♪ Blind♪

25:12.859 --> 25:15.644
♪ Every woman♪

25:15.688 --> 25:19.256
♪ Blind♪

25:20.606 --> 25:24.653
♪ Then you read ev...♪

25:27.700 --> 25:32.356
♪ You read ev...♪

25:32.400 --> 25:36.230
♪ ...very woman's mind♪

25:36.273 --> 25:41.409
♪ Ev...♪

25:43.411 --> 25:48.634
♪ ...very woman's♪

25:48.677 --> 25:51.506
♪ Mind.♪

